<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08190</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING AND MODERNIZING THE WAREHOUSE RECEIPTS LAW OF THE PHILIPPINES IN ORDER TO PROVIDE A LEGAL FRAMEWORK IN THE PHILIPPINES THAT SHALL FACILITATE TRADE, COMMERCE, AND OTHER RELATED PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Defines “Warehouse receipt” as a receipt, whether electronic or otherwise, issued by a warehouseman to release the goods to a specified person.

Proposes to establish a central electronic Registry for all Warehouse Receipts to be made readily available online, which shall be managed by a Warehousing Accreditation Council.  

Intends to enable the agricultural sector to “convert” goods and products into credit in a faster and simpler way, promote economic activity by increasing access to least cost credit by establishing a simplified, unified, and modern framework for the storage of goods in warehouses and the subsequent trading of interest therein.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GATCHALIAN, WES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-09-05</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2018-09-24)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-10-10)</td><tr><td>3. Bravo (M.) (000 2018-11-21)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRADE AND INDUSTRY ON 2018-09-11</td></tr></table>